modules.description: Provides type definitions for user and team identifiers, paths, and structured data like notes and permissions. Works with records representing users, teams, notes, and their metadata. Used to model protocol-specific data structures for request and response handling.

defines data structures for users, teams, notes, and permissions, with support for path manipulation and metadata handling. It includes operations to construct, parse, and transform these entities, enabling structured interaction with a markdown-based API. Examples include creating a note record, extracting a user ID from a path, or validating permission settings. The module serves as the foundation for API request and response modeling.

Provides functions to interact with the HackMD API, including creating, reading, updating, and deleting notes. Operates on data types such as notes, users, and authentication tokens. Enables programmatic access to collaborative document management and real-time editing features.

Encapsulates data models for users, teams, notes, and permissions, along with utilities for path and metadata manipulation. Supports constructing, parsing, and transforming entities to interact with a markdown-based API. Enables actions such as generating a note structure, extracting identifiers from paths, or verifying access controls. Provides a structured interface for API communication through typed representations.
